result.adr_address: 127 Electric Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 127 Electric Rd, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Camper's

reviews.text:
Delicious food, with many choices from Japanese kitchen. Supposedly the chef have 17 years experience from Japan before moving to Hong Kong to start this restaurant. 

It was a bit crowded with a queue outside, to tell about the popularity. 

vegetarian options in ample quantities, if you are into that short of thing.

Prices are cheap too compared to many other restaurants around and dishes are large enough. 2 dishes fit well for 2 persons.
Very great 15-type veggies curry rice! So colourful and healthy without MSG! And there’s sweet potato added into the rice! Yummy!
Great Japanese inspired menu, we had a beef curry and beef donburi. Both meals were delicious and the beef was flavoursome and melt in your mouth tender. Would definitely recommend!!
Homemade Japanese food. Vegetable is very fresh and tasty, not to mention the curry rice. Recommended!
Home-cooked food at it's best! Big servings and melts-in-your-mouth pork.

result.name: 坐忘

reviews.text: 好👌
都市下的甘泉😋
食物質素尚可，但調味略咸，招牌菜豬軟骨肉質亦不夠軟熟，令人失望。此外，員工服務態度非常惡劣，甚為囂張。不論食品質素還是員工服務皆遠不及鰂魚涌本店，決不再光顧此劣質分店。
